ds222rr_assign2.queue

Interface Queue

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedQueue

    public interface Queue
    This interface defines the functionality for a queue implementation. The functionality includes enqueuing elements in and dequeuing elements out from a Queue, as well as accessing the first and the last element of a Queue and to iterate all Node objects using an iterator. Illegal operations (calling first(), last() or dequeue() methods on queue having size = 0) should throw a RunTimeException.

    Author
